summary: An ordinance accepting a deed to the City of Seattle executed on July 16, 1910, by the Pacific States Lumber Company, by its Vice- President, F. L. Selleck, and its Secretary, J. G. Dickson, for lands in sections 18, 19, 20, 21, 22, 27, 28, 29, 30, 31, 32, 33, 34 and 35, Township 22 North, Range 8 East, W.M., in King County, State of Washington.
